[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Notability Notability] is the concept of how to determine what kinds of content is worth including in the wiki. While there are already rule governing the [[Special:MyLanguage/VRCWiki:Guidelines#Type_of_permitted_content|types of content permitted]] on this wiki as a whole, notability guidelines apply within those categories to govern specific pages and their inclusion.

Notability on the VRChat Wiki determines whether a subject merits its own article. Notability is a key principle to ensure that the content on the VRChat Wiki remains verifiable, relevant, and significant within the VRChat community. 

This is not a guarantee that a topic will necessarily be handled as a separate, stand-alone page. Editors may use their discretion to merge or group two or more related topics into a single article. These guidelines only outline how suitable a topic is for its own article or list. They do not limit the content of an article or list.

== Notability criteria for worlds ==
===Main namespace===
A world is considered notable enough to warrant an article in the Main namespace if it meets the following criteria:

*Official VRChat worlds
**Worlds created by official VRChat accounts (e.g. VRChat, Creator Support)

===Community namespace===
A world is considered notable enough to warrant an article in the Community namespace if it meets '''ONE''' of the following criteria:

*Statistical
**Worlds that have made it out of Community Labs AND
**have at least 10,000 visits or 1,000 favorites.
*Official VRChat social media & websites
**Social media content (e.g. Bluesky, X, YouTube)
**hello.vrchat.com & blog
**ask.vrchat.com posts made by a VRChat staff member (e.g. Developer Updates)
*Manually selected world rows 
**Spotlights (e.g. Marketplace tab spotlight, Spotlight - Mobile)
**Events (e.g. VRRat's Community Takeover, Drone Exploration)
*Partnered/Sponsored events
**Any world that's in a world row and/or has an accompanying "admin_" tag for said partnership/sponsored event (e.g. Virtual Market ("admin_vket2024w"), OKIVFES ("admin_okivfes2025")) 
*Jam winners
**Any world that's in a world row and/or has an accompanying "admin_" tag for said world jam (e.g. "admin_spacejam25_ssre", "admin_jam_sketchbook")
*Worlds included in official VRChat worlds
**Portals in the VRChat Home
**Jam hubs (e.g Spookality)
*Worlds that have had notable independent external coverage by reliable sources, such as [[Special:MyLanguage/Community:Treehouse in the Shade|Treehouse in the Shade]].

====Creator Economy worlds====
Worlds must meet the minimum statistical criteria, regardless of Creator Economy status.

==Notability criteria for avatars==
===Main namespace===
An avatar is considered notable enough to warrant an article in the Main namespace if it meets the following criteria:

*Official VRChat avatars
**Avatars created by official VRChat accounts (e.g. VRChat, Creator Support)

===Community namespace===
An avatar is considered notable enough to warrant an article in the Community namespace if it meets '''ONE''' of the following criteria:

*Official VRChat social media & websites
**Social media content (e.g. Bluesky, X, YouTube)
**hello.vrchat.com & blog
**ask.vrchat.com posts made by a VRChat staff member (e.g. Developer Updates)
*Manually selected avatar rows 
**Spotlights (e.g. Public, Legacy)
*Jam winners
**Any world that's in a avatar row and/or has an accompanying "admin_" tag for said avatar jam (e.g. "admin_spookality_24")
*Avatars included in official VRChat worlds
**Avatar pedestals in the VRChat Home
**Jam hubs (e.g Spookality)
*Notable avatars made by the community
**For a newly created Avatar page it should be obvious or made obvious that such Avatar or Avatar Type is notable enough. Therefore it is advised to create a [[VRCWiki:How to Contribute#Discussion Page|Discussion page]] right after a new Avatar page has been created with a note as for why the page was made. This helps to evaluate notability. Pages where this cannot be easily ascertained with may be deleted.

